<span id="freeTextContainer13010218387464111241">This is where I wish we had the option for 1/2 stars. It is really a 3.5 star read for me. It hit my creep factor from the first chapter. I find the ocean scary, boats, tiny little islands with no way off...so yes, it hit my personal creep factor. I enjoyed this tale. It may not be for many folks, who wants to read about <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[undead Nazi zombie mummies <a class='jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction'>(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> wreaking havoc on a tiny little island ? Oh, me, I raised my hand. The characters were all good, the token white woman </span>
  <span id="freeText13010218387464111241" style="display:none">This is where I wish we had the option for 1/2 stars. It is really a 3.5 star read for me. It hit my creep factor from the first chapter. I find the ocean scary, boats, tiny little islands with no way off...so yes, it hit my personal creep factor. I enjoyed this tale. It may not be for many folks, who wants to read about <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[undead Nazi zombie mummies <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> wreaking havoc on a tiny little island ? Oh, me, I raised my hand. The characters were all good, the token white woman was a bit flat, well, all the women were a bit flat, but this story didn't focus on them. It was about a police chief fighting his past, a white hotel owner, fighting his and then coming together. Oh and we have voodoo. Voodoo touches something, I am not sure what, it has power. Beware what you may reap when casting your voodoo spells. It is always about the unintended consequences. This is one you can just sit back and read and enjoy for what it is. </span>
