    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_501016440" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/501016440" />
    <a title="C. Conner" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4649884-c-conner"><img alt="C. Conner" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442509302p2/4649884.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/501016440?book_show_action=true">Jan 09, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="C. Conner" class="user" itemprop="url" name="C. Conner" href="/user/show/4649884-c-conner">C. Conner</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer501016440" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13441384093793802621">Not a good novel. Too much head hopping, too much back story, not a plausible plot or situation, boring characters....<br/><br/>40 something years after WWII an American trying to escape his traumatic past finds a German U-boat along the reef of an isolated Caribbean island. The diver dislodges a depth charge that explodes and releases the sub from the bottom. Point 1. An underwater explosion of that magnitude would have killed a scuba diver. Instead, he is taken to the surface by the rising sub. Point 2.</span>
  <span id="freeText13441384093793802621" style="display:none">Not a good novel. Too much head hopping, too much back story, not a plausible plot or situation, boring characters....<br /><br />40 something years after WWII an American trying to escape his traumatic past finds a German U-boat along the reef of an isolated Caribbean island. The diver dislodges a depth charge that explodes and releases the sub from the bottom. Point 1. An underwater explosion of that magnitude would have killed a scuba diver. Instead, he is taken to the surface by the rising sub. Point 2. Rising from depth that fast would have killed him, or at the very least given him a case of the bends for which he would need to be put in a hyperbaric chamber.<br /><br />The locals get some bad mojo coming from the sub but go ahead and tow it to the dock yard. The American and the local sheriff decide to explore inside and almost die when the crew comes to life and chases them out of the hatch. But not long after when a good looking (stereotypical) female professor flies in to survey the sub and demands to see it the American doesn't put up any resistance. If I almost got killed by a boat full of vengeful skeletons I would NOT go anywhere near it no matter how hot the professor looked.<br /><br />Some of the zombies terrorize the town and kill people but they also work to repair the submarine to get it sea worthy. The zombies are both falling apart into dust but somehow they are also super strong. They kill people and eat them but they also want to go back to sea and continue the fight for the Nazis. So at one point the village is getting ripped apart and the survivors are being chased through the jungle. Suddenly the zombies disappear and go back to the sub so they can wreck havoc on the shipping lanes.<br /><br />The main heroes are joined by some kind of local Carib leader and get on a hand-made boat in the middle of a storm of epic proportions to find the sub and sink it. While fighting the huge surging waves that threaten to capsize the boat they have time to argue with one another. The Carib leader dies and the American sacrifices himself to blow up the boat and the sub and he gets to rejoin his dead wife and kid who also drowned but in a different storm. The professor and the sheriff get on a floating piece of wood and make it to an island.<br /><br />These paragraphs pretty much sum up the highlights of the book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13441384093793802621" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

