<div id="review_2282693473" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2282693473" />
    <a title="Aaron Nash" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/45707654-aaron-nash"><img alt="Aaron Nash" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1511167493p2/45707654.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2282693473?book_show_action=true">Feb 05, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Aaron Nash" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Aaron Nash" href="/user/show/45707654-aaron-nash">Aaron Nash</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780380755981" href="/book/show/1072908.The_Night_Boat">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2282693473" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11423274651342196200">A quick review as i need to sleep! Ive just sat and read the best part of 60% of this novel. This is definitely the most fun ive had with a McCammon novel so far.<br/><br/>The book has a certain charm to it. Its fast paced and you can tell the author had to research or already knew a hell of a lot about boats and boat language. Many times there was terminology i didnt understand, but i still got what was going on so it didnt spoil the fun. The depths of the sea has always freaked me out and sea wrecks and</span>
  <span id="freeText11423274651342196200" style="display:none">A quick review as i need to sleep! Ive just sat and read the best part of 60% of this novel. This is definitely the most fun ive had with a McCammon novel so far.<br /><br />The book has a certain charm to it. Its fast paced and you can tell the author had to research or already knew a hell of a lot about boats and boat language. Many times there was terminology i didnt understand, but i still got what was going on so it didnt spoil the fun. The depths of the sea has always freaked me out and sea wrecks and ship ruins give me the jitters. The submarine that rises in this novel was described perfectly and made me feel very uneasy whilst i was reading it. If you can make a submarine creepy then thats a good job in my eyes and McCammon definitely succeeded there. The first half was very atmospheric and built that feeling of dread extremely well. <br /><br />Surprisingly though i enjoyed the book a lot more before the action started. Yes there are some great gory set pieces, but they're similar in tone and nothing you havent read before. Luckily though the story doesnt drag and the ending, whilst predictable, was still very enjoyable. <br /><br />This one is well worth your time. I have now read the first four of McCammons disowned novels in the space of a month and this is the best of the bunch.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11423274651342196200" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


